Mexico signed a rescheduling accordcovering 120 mln dlrs in official debts to Britain, as part ofa 1.8 billion dlr restructuring agreed with the Paris club ofcreditors last year, the finance ministry said.    The rescheduling is over 10 years with five years grace,and carries an interest margin of 1/2 pct over libor.    Finance minister Gustavo Petricioli, who signed the accordfor Mexico, said the agreement reflects a strengthening ofeconomic, financial and trade relations between the twocountries.    The Paris Club restructuring forms part of a 12 billion dlrfinancial package agreed with Mexico's creditors last year.    The rescheduling covers public sector trade debts comingdue between september 1986 and march 1988. Reuter&#3;